org.ndnx.ndn.impl.sync
Class SyncNodeCache

java.lang.Object
  org.ndnx.ndn.impl.sync.SyncNodeCache

public class SyncNodeCache
extends Object

Nodes can be cached by hash across different comparators. We use WeakReferences to avoid accidentally caching nodes that no longer have any real referents. Since we only need to request nodes once per slice, the pending mechanism should be global

pending

public SyncNodeCache.Pending pending(byte[] hash)
Activate the mechanism to avoid multiple requests for the same node and to wait for a node in the process of being fetched by another comparator if it is. This is a "get and set" routine which creates and stores a lock for sharing if one hasn't already been created for this hash. The caller must acquire or attempt to acquire the lock. The first caller should request the node and notify waiters when it has it. Subsequent callers will wait for the node to return by acquiring the lock.

Parameters:
hash -
Returns:
Lock object for waiting for the node
